1Ô∏è‚É£ Problem Statement (ADD THIS)

Paste this into your documentation file:

Problem Statement

Urban areas face increasing challenges such as traffic congestion, deteriorating environmental conditions, and delayed responses to abnormal situations. Traditional urban management systems often operate in isolation and lack real-time data processing capabilities, leading to inefficient monitoring and delayed decision-making.

There is a need for an integrated digital platform that can ingest real-time urban sensor data, analyze conditions dynamically, generate alerts based on predefined thresholds, and provide predictive insights to support data-driven urban governance.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Objectives of the Project (VERY IMPORTANT)

Add this section:

Objectives

The primary objectives of this project are:

To design and implement a backend platform for smart city monitoring

To ingest and validate real-time sensor data representing traffic and environmental conditions

To generate priority-aware alerts based on predefined thresholds

To predict traffic congestion levels using explainable analytics

To simulate real-time IoT data streams for testing and demonstration

To ensure scalability and extensibility for future integration with real IoT hardware and machine learning models

3Ô∏è‚É£ Methodology (EXAMINERS LOVE THIS)

Paste this exactly:

Methodology

The system follows a modular and layered methodology:

Data Acquisition
Sensor data is obtained through a Python-based IoT simulator that emulates real-time traffic and environmental sensors.

Data Validation
Incoming data is validated using structured Pydantic models to ensure consistency and correctness.

Data Processing
Validated data is processed through rule-based analytics to evaluate alert conditions and predict traffic congestion levels.

Alert Generation
Alerts are generated dynamically using predefined thresholds and classified by priority.

Visualization & Testing
System functionality is verified through API documentation and live simulator outputs.

